Blocks.childText: 1885 Gold 28 Schl SALUTATORY. IN the accompanying work the Author has sought to embrace in a convenient shape, a varied collection of orignal Sacred Songs and Hymns, which will supply to Sabbath-schools, Praise Meetings, and Home Circles popular selections, from which everything inap- propriate to special and general uses has been eliminated, and in which the music will be found in closest sympathy with the sentiment. THE GOLDEN SHEAF, No. I, will be followed by other numbers of uniform size and shape, and at the same popular price, which will enable those using them to renew and obtain fresh Songs and Hymns at proper intervals. THE GOLDEN SHEAF, No. I, can be had at $12.00 per ( 100); or, I5 cents a single copy, bound in board covers; or, $9.00 per (100); or, IO cents a single copy, bound in paper covers, upon ap- plication to the publisher. O. W. SCHAEFFER, Romney, W. Va. This work having been copyrighted, no selection contained in it can be published without the written consent of the Author. J. M. ARMSTRONG & CO., MUSIC TYPOGRAPHERS, Philadelphia, Pa.
